{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody knew that he was Jewish, but he was hit during the bombardment in Polish uprising, and he probably died in the hospital during uprising because we looked for him, one of my aunts and myself, in Warsaw in April '45 after the war.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we found as much that he was hit by that bomb and that they took him to the hospital, and then there were the other traces.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, not six.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We stayed until--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About five years.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Five years after the war to-- to early '50, yes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But of course there were many.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were many who-- there were some people who survived the war like us, and there were quite a lot who came from the Soviet Union who survived the war because-- what I said in the beginning was that lots of Jews who were deported in early-- in early years, in 1940, 1941, like my aunt Dora and my grandfather, to Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They went to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had terrible conditions there, but most of them survived the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And not my grandmother, because she died in Uzbekistan in Central Asia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But most of them did survive the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And lots of them came back to Poland after the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And not so many to Warsaw, maybe, but many came to Silesia, other parts of Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But most of them emigrated in the years after, but it was not always possible to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Emigrated means that that had to be with the agreement of the authorities.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that agreement was sometimes given and sometimes not, so there were periods when Jews were allowed to emigrate and there were long periods when they were not allowed to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were allowed to emigrate immediately after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
